#18733
The Baker's Storage~
   The floor space not covered by large powdery burlap sacks is nearly
patterned with the flour dusted footprints of the cook.  Rough-hewn wooden
shelves line the entire room, except for a tiny window on the western wall.  
A small preparation table sits in the southeast corner containing various
bowls of wet and dry substances.  
~
